main event: An unidentified object was observed at Cambria AFS, California, on 23 August 1957, initially thought to be related to astronomical bodies.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 30 minutes,The object was motionless at first before moving laterally, Ground radar confirmed the visual observation of the object, Sighting initially considered an aircraft but later assessed as possibly a weather balloon or natural phenomena, A total of two objects were reported during the sighting.
witness description: observers from the 775th ACW Squadron, including radar operators and officers
